{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo","doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/$volume","doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/Your-First-Data-Source"],["doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo"]],"modules":[{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Creating-the-Data-Source"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Building-the-Dice-View"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Rolling-Automatically"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/Your-First-Data-Source"},{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Setting-Up-the-Dice-Service"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Choosing-the-Right-Refresh-Policy"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Adding-a-Second-Dependency"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Bridging-Streams-to-SwiftUI"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Building-the-Roll-View"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/Reactive-Dependencies"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"project","metadata":{"category":"Silo","categoryPathComponent":"Silo","role":"project","title":"Rolling a D6"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/silo\/buildingad6diceroller"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[{"chapter":"Your First Data Source","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this tutorial, you will build a D6 dice roller using Silo. The fetch is a single line — ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int.random(in: 1...6)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — so every concept you encounter is focused on Silo, with no boilerplate distractions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You will create a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo\/DataSource","type":"reference"},{"text":" backed by a random number, drive a SwiftUI view from its reactive stream, wire up a Roll button, and configure the die to roll itself automatically while the view is on screen.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"hero","title":"Rolling a D6","estimatedTimeInMinutes":15},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"anchor":"Creating-the-Data-Source","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceRoller"},{"type":"text","text":" service that holds a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo\/DataSource","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the last roll. Because the current roll may be absent before the die is first rolled, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int?"},{"type":"text","text":" is the appropriate type — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" means “not yet rolled.”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" is one of Silo’s built-in empty types, so no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"emptyValue"},{"type":"text","text":" closure is needed. The source starts as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and updates to a number each time "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"title":"Creating the Data Source","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceRoller.swift"},{"type":"text","text":". Define an empty "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceRoller"},{"type":"text","text":" class marked "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@MainActor"},{"type":"text","text":" with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shared"},{"type":"text","text":" singleton."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"code":"DiceRoller-01.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lastRoll"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo\/DataSource","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The fetch closure returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int.random(in: 1...6)"},{"type":"text","text":". The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onError"},{"type":"text","text":" handler returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".keep"},{"type":"text","text":" so that any error preserves the previous roll value."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task.sleep"},{"type":"text","text":" delay is artificial — it simulates a slow fetch so the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProgressView"},{"type":"text","text":" added in the next section remains visible during development. A real fetch would call a network API here instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"DiceRoller-02.swift","runtimePreview":null}]},{"anchor":"Building-the-Dice-View","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Subscribe to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo\/DataSource\/valueWithState","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" in a SwiftUI view. This stream delivers a snapshot on every change — value or loading state — so one subscription drives both the roll display and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProgressView"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".task"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier iterates the stream for as long as the view is on screen. When the view disappears, the task is cancelled automatically — a behaviour that becomes relevant when auto-roll is introduced in the next section."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"title":"Building the Dice View","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceView.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" with a reference to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceRoller.shared"},{"type":"text","text":" and a placeholder body."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"code":"DiceView-01.swift","runtimePreview":"DiceView-01.png"},{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" properties for the current roll and loading state. In "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".task"},{"type":"text","text":", iterate "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"roller.lastRoll.valueWithState"},{"type":"text","text":" and update state from each snapshot. Show the roll as a large number — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" renders as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"—\""},{"type":"text","text":" before the first roll — and a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProgressView"},{"type":"text","text":" while the source is refreshing."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"code":"DiceView-02.swift","runtimePreview":"DiceView-02.png"},{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a Roll button that calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh(clear: true)"},{"type":"text","text":". Passing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clear: true"},{"type":"text","text":" sets "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lastRoll"},{"type":"text","text":" back to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" immediately, so the display returns to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"—\""},{"type":"text","text":" while the next number is being generated — a clear visual cue that a new roll is in flight."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"code":"DiceView-03.swift","runtimePreview":"DiceView-03.png"}]},{"anchor":"Rolling-Automatically","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".autoRefresh(.seconds(2))"},{"type":"text","text":" to roll the die automatically every two seconds while the view is visible. The timer is subscriber-driven: it starts when the first subscriber appears on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lastRoll.values"},{"type":"text","text":" and stops when the last one disappears."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".task"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceView"},{"type":"text","text":" cancels when the view leaves the screen, the auto-roll timer stops automatically — no manual cleanup is required."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"title":"Rolling Automatically","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".autoRefresh(.seconds(2))"},{"type":"text","text":" before "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".build()"},{"type":"text","text":". The view requires no changes: the existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"valueWithState"},{"type":"text","text":" subscription picks up each automatic roll as it arrives."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"code":"DiceRoller-03.swift","runtimePreview":null}]}]},{"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","assessments":[{"content":[],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lastRoll"},{"text":" is typed as ","type":"text"},{"code":"DataSource<Int?>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". What does ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represent?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An error occurred during the last roll."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Errors are handled separately by the ","type":"text"},{"code":"onError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closure, not encoded as ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value comes from Silo’s built-in empty state for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" types — it simply means the source has never been fetched."}]}],"isCorrect":false},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The die has not been rolled yet, or the value was cleared."}]}],"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is one of Silo’s built-in empty types. The source starts as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and stays "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"type":"text","text":" is first called — or after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh(clear: true)"},{"text":" resets it while a new roll is in flight.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":true},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto-roll is disabled."}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Auto-roll is configured via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".autoRefresh()"},{"type":"text","text":" on the builder, not encoded in the value type. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" means the source has no value yet, regardless of whether auto-roll is on or off."}]}]}]},{"content":[],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh(clear: true)"},{"type":"text","text":" and then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh(clear: true)"},{"type":"text","text":" again immediately. How many rolls happen?"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two rolls — one for each call.","type":"text"}]}],"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Concurrent ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"text":" calls are deduplicated. The second caller joins the in-flight task started by the first and awaits its result — only one roll ever happens.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One roll — the second call joins the in-flight task."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Silo deduplicates concurrent refreshes. The second ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"text":" call detects an active task and awaits it instead of starting a new one. Both callers receive the same result.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Zero rolls — the second call cancels the first.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calls are deduplicated, not cancelled. The in-flight task runs to completion and both callers receive the result."}]}]}]},{"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The timer stops automatically because there are no more subscribers.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Auto-refresh is subscriber-driven. The ","type":"text"},{"code":".task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier in ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiceView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" cancels when the view disappears, removing the last subscriber from ","type":"text"},{"code":"lastRoll.values","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". With no subscribers, the timer stops — no manual cleanup is needed."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The timer keeps running in the background indefinitely.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The timer is subscriber-driven, not a free-running background process. It only runs while at least one subscriber is active on the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"values"},{"text":" stream.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The timer stops, but only if you call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidate()"},{"text":" on the ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiceRoller","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No manual invalidation is needed. Silo tracks the subscriber count automatically and stops the timer when it reaches zero.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You configure "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".autoRefresh(.seconds(2))"},{"type":"text","text":". The user navigates away and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceView"},{"type":"text","text":" disappears. What happens to the timer?"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[]}]},{"action":{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"Get started","type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies","isActive":true},"kind":"callToAction","featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","title":"Reacting to Dice Configuration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh poli